The baseline visit occurred 47 days out of window. As per protocol, the baseline was supposed to be completed by 01/03/2019, but due to lack of pt. availability during the holiday season and difficulties arranging out of state travel, the baseline was not conducted until 2/19/19, placing the visit 47 days out of window. The local IRB will be notified during the next ongoing review. GDT 2/20/19

According to the laboratory manual, Red and lavender top tubes collected fro bio marker analysis should be centrifuged within 60 minutes of collection. Staff was unable to process according to these guidelines as they were accompanying the participant to his lumbar puncture immediately following the blood collection.  Tubes were collected at 6:38 am and were not centrifuged until 8:45 am. The IRB will be informed of this deviation during the next continuing review. GDT 2/20/19
